## Calculate CI for population [**slope**]{style="color:green"} $\beta_1$

::: columns
::: {.column width="50%"}
$$b_1 \pm t^*\cdot SE_{b_1}$$
:::

::: {.column width="50%"}
where $t^*$ is the $t$-distribution critical value with $df = n -2$.
:::
